    <text><body>
            <div type="writingSession">
                <pb n="1r"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000407 https://www.geonames.org/2645740">Kew</placeName> May 12<hi rendition="#sup"><hi rendition="#u">th</hi></hi> 185<subst>
                            <del rendition="#ow">4</del>
                            <add place="across">5</add>
                        </subst></dateline><note place="right" hand="https://edition-humboldt.de/addressee"><foreign xml:lang="deu">Dr Joseph Hooker <lb/>Sohn von <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Sir William <lb/>Hooker</persName>, <lb/>war am <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0010385 https://www.geonames.org/6942239">Südpol</placeName><supplied cert="high">,</supplied>
                            <lb/>am <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0006863 https://www.geonames.org/1252558">Himalaya</placeName> und <lb/>in
                                <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0009370 https://www.geonames.org/1279685">Tibet</placeName><supplied cert="high">.</supplied></foreign></note>
                    <salute>My dear friend</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You will I am sure be <lb/>kindly glad to hear that the <lb/><choice>
                        <sic>Goverment</sic>
                        <corr>Government</corr>
                    </choice> have been pleased <lb/>to recognize my <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Father</persName>’s &amp; my <lb/>services, &amp; have at last granted
                    <lb/>me a position <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">of</del>
                        <add place="across">at</add>
                    </subst>
                    <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000407 https://www.geonames.org/2645740">Kew</placeName>, appointing <lb/>me Assistant Director
                    of the <lb/><orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000559 http://d-nb.info/gnd/1018641-4">Royal Gardens</orgName> (to my <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Father</persName>), <lb/>with a salary of <measure quantity="400" unit="pfund_sterling">£ 400</measure> a year. <lb/>This is I
                    need hardly say a <lb/>matter of great rejoicing to us <lb/>all, as it affords
                    hopes to my <lb/><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Father</persName> that I may
                    eventually <lb/>succeed him, should my <lb/>services be approved; &amp; for
                    <lb/>the present it ensures me <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow"><gap quantity="1" unit="words" reason="covered"/></del>
                        <add place="across">the</add>
                    </subst>
                    <lb/>enjoyment <subst>
                        <del rendition="#s">for the</del>
                        <add place="superlinear">(as also in</add>
                    </subst> future<add place="intralinear">)</add> of an <lb/>income that enables
                    me to <lb/>devote my whole time to<pb n="1v"/>science. It is now many <lb/>years
                    since my <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011993 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11698094X">Father</persName> has <lb/>been vainly
                    endeavoring to <lb/>procure any fixed position <lb/>for me, in connection with
                    <lb/>the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000559 http://d-nb.info/gnd/1018641-4">Royal Gardens</placeName>, but except <lb/>in
                    the shape of occasional <lb/>grants for special services I <lb/>have never
                    received any <lb/>support<choice>
                        <orig>.</orig>
                        <reg/>
                    </choice> from the <placeName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000559 http://d-nb.info/gnd/1018641-4">Gardens</placeName>, in <lb/>which
                    I have been so long <lb/>engaged.</p>
                <p>And now I am going to <lb/>beg a great favor of you &amp; hope <lb/>that you will
                    pardon me if <lb/>my request is unreasonable, <lb/>&amp; that is that you would
                    <lb/>send to my <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9236694 https://viaf.org/viaf/198146998388318941056">wife</persName> a portrait <lb/>of
                    yourself to hang up in <lb/>our Drawing room. We are <lb/>quite envious <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">&amp;</del>
                        <add place="across">of</add>
                    </subst>
                    <add place="superlinear">the one you have sent to</add>
                    <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0015345 http://d-nb.info/gnd/11671350X"><choice>
                            <abbr>Col.</abbr>
                            <expan>Colonel</expan>
                        </choice> Sabine</persName>’s <lb/>&amp; if <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">I</del>
                        <add place="across">we</add>
                    </subst> could have procured one<pb n="2r"/>without troubling you we <lb/>should
                    have done so. Perhaps <lb/>if you can spare one you will <lb/>kindly write Mrs
                        <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9236694 https://viaf.org/viaf/198146998388318941056">Hooker</persName>’s name <lb/>on it, that she may
                    have a <lb/>memorial of you herself.</p>
                <p>I have searched in vain for <lb/>any more information about <lb/>the <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Sargassum</name></hi>; &amp; for
                    experiments <lb/>upon its vitality in a basin of <lb/>water. I shall however
                    endeavor <lb/>to settle the point by having <lb/>some specimens brought home
                    <lb/>in a bucket of salt water, &amp; <lb/>sent to the salt-water Vivarium
                    <lb/>in the <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H1884631">Regent’s Park Zoological
                        <lb/>Gardens</orgName>. I cannot see any <lb/>difficulty in supposing that
                    <lb/>this <name type="plant" key="algae">Alga</name> maintains an inde<g ref="#typoHyphen"/><lb break="no"/>pendent existence, floating as <lb/>well
                    as attached, as I know <lb/>that <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Fucus
                            servatus</name></hi>, <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant" key="Fucus nodosus">nodosus</name></hi>,<pb n="2v"/>&amp; <hi rendition="#u"><name type="plant">Macrocystis pyrifera</name></hi> do.</p>
                <p>The <choice>
                        <sic>Goverment</sic>
                        <corr>Government</corr>
                    </choice> have been <lb/>very liberal to <orgName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0000559 http://d-nb.info/gnd/1018641-4">Kew</orgName>
                    this year, <lb/>voting ample sums to the support <lb/>of the <subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">l</del>
                        <add place="across">L</add>
                    </subst>ive plants, Museum, <lb/><subst>
                        <del rendition="#ow">l</del>
                        <add place="across">L</add>
                    </subst>ibrary &amp; Herbarium; also <lb/><measure quantity="1800" unit="pfund_sterling">£ 1800</measure> for building a new conser<g ref="#typoHyphen"/><lb break="no"/>vatory &amp; <measure quantity="3000" unit="pfund_sterling">£ 3000</measure> for a new <lb/>Museum; this, with my
                    <lb/>appointment, was quite unexpected, <lb/>considering the extent of the
                        <lb/><ref xml:id="ac8f4b5c-65ab-407b-8f4b-5c65ab607be8" corresp="#aa23dea7-c941-4636-a3de-a7c941a63649" type="editorialNote">War</ref><note xml:id="aa23dea7-c941-4636-a3de-a7c941a63649" corresp="#ac8f4b5c-65ab-407b-8f4b-5c65ab607be8" type="editorial">Hiermit ist der Krimkrieg von 1853 bis 1856
                            gemeint.</note> estimate especially.</p>
                <p>I shall have the pleasure <lb/>of sending to you next week <lb/>the first volume
                    of the <ref xml:id="a7d5895a-c108-445b-9589-5ac108845b58" corresp="#cb24ae95-3f27-47c2-a4ae-953f2787c22a" type="editorialNote">„Flora <lb/>Indica“</ref><note xml:id="cb24ae95-3f27-47c2-a4ae-953f2787c22a" corresp="#a7d5895a-c108-445b-9589-5ac108845b58" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/VNWTINB4">Hooker, J.
                                D./Thomson 1855</bibl>, I.</note> in which you will find <lb/>a <ref xml:id="dbe28b15-39ed-464d-a28b-1539edf64de8" corresp="#b135b4e3-3b53-4d57-b5b4-e33b534d57e5" type="editorialNote">sketch of the Physical Geography <lb/>of the whole area, &amp; of each
                            province</ref><note xml:id="b135b4e3-3b53-4d57-b5b4-e33b534d57e5" corresp="#dbe28b15-39ed-464d-a28b-1539edf64de8" type="editorial"><bibl corresp="https://edition-humboldt.de/VNWTINB4">Hooker, J.
                                D./Thomson 1855</bibl>, I, S. 83–258: "Sketch of the Physical
                            Features and Vegetation of the Provinces of India".</note>, <lb/>by <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0003944 http://d-nb.info/gnd/117351946">D.<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>
                        Thomson</persName> &amp; myself.</p>
                <p>Mrs <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9236694 https://viaf.org/viaf/198146998388318941056">Hooker</persName> desires her most <lb/>respectful
                    remembrances &amp; regrets that <lb/>she has never yet seen you – she &amp; the
                        <lb/><ref xml:id="a5c21dc3-07fd-447a-821d-c307fd247ac3" corresp="#f0acbb96-aa33-4f4e-acbb-96aa331f4e17" type="editorialNote">children</ref><note xml:id="f0acbb96-aa33-4f4e-acbb-96aa331f4e17" corresp="#a5c21dc3-07fd-447a-821d-c307fd247ac3" type="editorial">Der Sohn <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H6906554">William
                                Henslow</persName> wurde 1853 und die Tochter <persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H9813752">Harriet Anne</persName> wurde 1854 geboren.</note> are all well.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Believe me with profound respect <lb/>ever your affectionate
                        pupil</salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="https://edition-humboldt.de/H0011992 http://d-nb.info/gnd/118774891">J.D. Hooker</persName></signed>. </closer>
            </div>
        </body></text>
